## 4. Treat predictor as continuous: check linearity assumption (1/2)

- You may think we need to look at the fitted log-odds to check linearity
  - BUT fitted log-odds were constrained to the linearity assumption, so it will automatically be linear!



::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
newdata = data.frame(x = c(1, 2, 3)) 
pred = predict(ex1_cont_glm, newdata, se.fit=T, type = "link")
LL_CI1 = pred$fit - qnorm(1-0.05/2) * pred$se.fit
UL_CI1 = pred$fit + qnorm(1-0.05/2) * pred$se.fit

pred_link = data.frame(x = newdata, Pred = pred$fit, LL_CI1, UL_CI1) 
```
